---
import BaseHead from '@src/components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '@src/components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '@src/consts';
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />

    <style>
      .title {
        margin-bottom: 1em;
        padding: 1em 0;
        text-align: center;
        line-height: 1;
      }
      .title h1 {
        margin: 0 0 0.5em 0;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <Header title={SITE_TITLE} />

    <main>
      <div class="title">
        <h1>Principles</h1>

        <hr />
      </div>

      <ul>
        <li>Provide 100% valid HTML</li>

        <li>Write <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/Semantics">semantic HTML/CSS/JS</a></li>

        <li>Prefer native elements, properties or APIs before external libraries</li>

        <li>Use <a href="https://dev.to/stakedesigner/best-practices-for-naming-classes-in-html-and-css-files-2kb5">meaningful class names</a></li>

        <li>The <a href="https://web.dev/articles/vitals?hl=en">performance</a> is important</li>

        <li>Think about the needs of the person which will use your code, the user experience(UX) and the developer experience(DX)</li>

        <li>Use elements, properties or APIs with sufficient browser support, required by the task you are working on</li>

        <li>Follow the general <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/frontend-development-best-practices-code-structure-adekola-olawale">best practices</a> in web development</li>
      </ul>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
